#summary Overview of ANSEL (and ADCON) register layout

= Table of ANSELx (and ADCON) registers and their bit fileds =
  - Only PICs with ADC-module and ANSELx or ADCONx listed.
  - First column contains PIC name and number of AN channels.
  - Second column contains the control register.
  - Following columns are the bits (numbered left to right!), containing:
    * bitname of the control register,
    * the "x" in the corresponding names pin_ANx and JANSEL_ANSx,
    * the physical pin of pin_ANx (from pinmap.py)
      ("---" no pin_ANx, not in pinmap file, something wrong).
